<p>FYI Arch Linux is not Slackware based&#8230; it is incompatible with Slackware.</p>
<p>And I do not panic. I just do not have much time to spend on re-writing stuff that used to work and then breaks because a software release policy changes. I think it is a waste of precious time.</p>
<p>However, I do want to have KDE 4.7.0 available for Slackware. Since that is only a matter of finding enough available free time, it was inevitable that I would do the re-write at some point. Holiday periods are good for that.</p>
<p>Since last night, I have a set of KDE 4.7.0 packages, created by a rewritten and modular KDE SlackBuild. I needed proof that the script works, and I have that proof now.<br />
So I am rebuilding the packages now (for both ARCH-es) in order to test the new release before uploading the packages.</p>
<p>Eric</p>
